# Regression with TS
library(forecast)
library(tseries)

# data
sales_data <- read.csv('./data/ts_reg_s1.csv')
head(sales_data)
##   Store       Date Sales Customers Open Promo SchoolHoliday
## 1     1 2013-08-01  4994       555    1     1             1
## 2     1 2013-08-02  4494       562    1     1             1
## 3     1 2013-08-03  4461       553    1     0             1
## 4     1 2013-08-04     0         0    0     0             1
## 5     1 2013-08-05  4086       522    1     0             1
## 6     1 2013-08-06  3582       477    1     0             1
ts.plot(sales_data$Sales)

# train, test
sales_train <- sales_data[1:89,]
sales_test <- sales_data[90:96,]

# lm
sales_lm <- lm(Sales ~ Open+Promo+SchoolHoliday, data= sales_train)
summary(sales_lm)

# prediction

sales_lm_fcst <- predict(sales_lm, newdata=sales_test[, covariates])

# ARIMA   - 
sales_train <- ts(sales_train, frequency=7) #   

# ARIMA 
sales_fit1 <- auto.arima(sales_train[, "Sales"])
sales_forecast1 <- forecast(sales_fit1, h=7)

# 1-MAPE
mean(100 - 100*abs(as.numeric(sales_forecast1$mean[-4]) - as.numeric(sales_test$Sales[-4])) / as.numeric(sales_test$Sales[-4]))
## [1] 91.38862

Regression with ARIMA errors

  1. x , ARIMA .

  2. auto.arima , auto.airma(data, xreg) xreg x .

  3. ARIMA forecast xreg .

# Regression With ARIMA errors
# ARIMA + Regression
covariates <- c("Open", "Promo", "SchoolHoliday")
sales_fit2 <- auto.arima(sales_train[,"Sales"], xreg=sales_train[,covariates])

# forecasting
sales_fcst <- forecast(sales_fit2, xreg=ts(sales_test[, covariates])) # test   ts  . auto.arima  . 
plot(sales_fcst)

mean(100 - 100*abs(as.numeric(sales_fcst$mean[-4]) - as.numeric(sales_test$Sales[-4])) / as.numeric(sales_test$Sales[-4]))
## [1] 90.59879
